    <title type="html"><![CDATA[Vim won't let you paste properly?]]></title>
    <link href="http://abh1nav.github.io/blog/2012/12/21/vim-paste-indent-fail/"/>
    <updated>2012-12-21T00:45:03-05:00</updated>
    <id>http://abh1nav.github.io/blog/2012/12/21/vim-paste-indent-fail</id>
    <content type="html"><![CDATA[<p>When you paste in vim, if the indents look funny, then before you paste, run:</p>

<figure class='code'><div class="highlight"><table><tr><td class="gutter"><pre class="line-numbers"><span class='line-number'>1</span>
</pre></td><td class='code'><pre><code class='vim'><span class='line'><span class="p">:</span><span class="k">set</span> <span class="nb">paste</span>
</span></code></pre></td></tr></table></div></figure>


<p>make sure you&rsquo;re in insert mode, do paste, then</p>

<figure class='code'><div class="highlight"><table><tr><td class="gutter"><pre class="line-numbers"><span class='line-number'>1</span>
</pre></td><td class='code'><pre><code class='vim'><span class='line'><span class="p">:</span><span class="k">set</span> <span class="nb">nopaste</span>
</span></code></pre></td></tr></table></div></figure>


<p>and continue editing.</p>
]]></content>
